The driver of a Nissan carrying foreign national missionaries that was traveling in the Johannesburg direction, lost control of the the vehicle and collided with a truck and a taxi.The taxi was full of passengers that sustained light injuries. The driver of the truck is unharmed, but his passenger was taken to the hospital for minor injuries.A missionary of the Nissan died on the scene. The deceased appeared to be a New Zealand national. Two other missionaries appeared to be American, and one from Samoa.SAPS could not confirm identities of the deceased or the other inhabitants of the Nissan at the time.*Lowvelder previously reported the Nissan to be a Mercedes Benz, this was an error.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;